        <p>In recent years, evidence has accumulated that physical exercise can improve fatigue, oxygen consumption, various aspects of QoL, depression and walking 
            distance in PwMS<sup>65,66,67,68</sup>. A recent German study highlighted that rehabilitation via long-term endurance exercise improves aerobic capacity in patients 
            with RRMS which in turn improved levels of fatigue<sup>69</sup>. </p>
